&lt;p&gt;DIRECTORATE OF ORAL SERVICES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANT IN PAEDIATRIC DENTISTRY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Consultant in Paediatric Dentistry at the Charles Clifford Dental Hospital, part of the Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post and offers an excellent opportunity for a highly motivated and enthusiastic Consultant in Paediatric Dentistry. The appointee, together with Consultant colleagues, will be responsible for the provision of a Paediatric Dentistry service for the residents of Sheffield and surrounding areas and for the teaching of undergraduates in the School of Clinical Dentistry and junior staff within the department and postgraduates, as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have full GDC registration, completed Specialist Training and be entered on the Specialist Register of the GDC or have a CCST date in Paediatric Dentistry within six months of the date of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMs Halla ZaitounAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ms Halla Zaitoun&lt;/strong&gt;, Clinical Lead for Paediatric Dentistry on (0114) 271 7882 or Professor A. Loescher, Clinical Director, telephone 0114 271 7804&lt;/p&gt;
